&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>How To Change Your GitHub Theme</title><link>http://localhost:1313/posts/how-to-change-your-github-theme/</link><pubDate>Sun, 04 Apr 2021 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/how-to-change-your-github-theme/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;So, as you may or may not know, &lt;a href="https://github.com/"&gt;GitHub&lt;/a&gt; is testing themes for its website, and the feature is now in beta according to &lt;a href="https://docs.github.com/en/github/setting-up-and-managing-your-github-user-account/managing-your-theme-settings"&gt;GitHub Docs&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To change how your &lt;a href="https://github.com/"&gt;GitHub&lt;/a&gt; looks, you need to log in to your &lt;a href="https://github.com/"&gt;GitHub&lt;/a&gt; account, click your profile pictures, choose &lt;em&gt;Settings&lt;/em&gt; &amp;gt; &lt;em&gt;Appearance&lt;/em&gt; and on the section that opens, choose one of the three themes that are currently available.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Below are the screen shots, courtesy of &lt;a href="https://docs.github.com/en/github/setting-up-and-managing-your-github-user-account/managing-your-theme-settings"&gt;GitHub Docs&lt;/a&gt;:
&lt;figure&gt;&lt;img src="http://localhost:1313/images/github-theme-userbar-account-settings.webp"
 alt="GitHub Account Settings" width="75%" height="75%"&gt;&lt;figcaption&gt;
 &lt;h4&gt;GitHub Account Settings&lt;/h4&gt;
